This paper deals with voting rules and axioms in the context of committee selection, which is a topic that falls under the category of computational social choice (cs.GT). The paper also discusses algorithmic problems related to committee selection, which could be classified under machine learning (cs.AI) or data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). The use of voting rules and the analysis of their properties also relates to topics in machine learning (cs.LG) and multi-agent systems (cs.MA).
